The paper focuses on content-based image retrieval (CBIR) using deep learning methods, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of sparse representation and dimensionality reduction techniques, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper compares different features and similarity measures, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
